<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
When the translation defines use_accept4 as a static constant (for example when USE_ACCEPT4 is defined and _DEBUG is not), use_accept4 is always true and the controlling expression (! use_accept4 && (MHD_INVALID_SOCKET != (s = accept(...)))) is invariant (always false). This makes the if condition a compile-time constant and so violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3 (the allowed exceptions do not apply).
</scenario>

